column49: It is very disappointing that I have collected my own funds through donations from family, friends, and other sponsors but I am limited on which books I can make available to my students.  I have enough support to offer students a $2 book each month for 10 months.  There should be more than one book each month for me to choose from.  I understand that the cost of many things have increased but I do not think that I can create life long readers without choice of books.  In the past, the discount store opened when you spent so much.  At least then, I could offer at least three different books to my students to choose from.  Now, there is only one.  I am dedicated to my profession and using your company to receive the books for my students.  It would just be nice to be able to access more books for a discounted rate.

In the past I have had many parents that would purchase one book in each order for their child.  They are now saying if they have to buy a bundle they will buy less often. I have many families that are ESL and are unable to do all the navigating on the website.  The form was much easier to fill out!  Now I know I will lose out on orders.  Also, why on earth can we not choose our own date to get their order in?  I certainly do not want to wait three weeks.  Parents want to get the books ordered and come in a timely manner, and not have to wait for over a month for books to come in!  I am very upset Scholastic.  You totally dropped the ball.  Also, I would never give out my parents email addresses to you!

column49: There have been to many changes made. The new flyers were a flop with my parents. I usualy have a large book order the first two months. No one has ordered. I also do not like that I can't set my own due date. The closer to the first of the month is always better for my parents. Not the middle of the month. There are not enough bargain books listed. I have been a huge fan of scholastic for a long time but I am disappointed in all the new changes. I think you'll see I am not the only one. The parents could care less about the coloring and  added puzzles. They want books offered at a discount and not everyone wants to order online. I am very sad - that I didn't even have one order! You can look in the past and see where I always have between 2 and 3 hundred dollars on my first few orders. Even parents of past siblings have told me that they will not be ordering because they can get the books cheaper at walmart and on Amazon. Such a shame.

It is also not convenient for parents who do not  have access or prefer to not order online.  In the past I would place orders for them.  Now they don't have an order form to submit to me. column49: Hello!  I am a 17 year veteran teacher and have been a satisfied patron of Scholastic for all the years I have been an educator.  One thing I really valued as a teacher was the option of Target gift cards purchased with bonus points.  There are specific supplies (such as a certain brand of folders, binders or brand specific art supplies) and classroom materials for my classroom to maximize the learning opportunities for my students.  Those items would be bought with the Target gift cards and I found that to be super useful & helpful - especially working at an urban school with minimal funding.  Please consider bringing the Target gift cards back...or consider other forms of gift cards such as Amazon. Thank you!!

column49: I am very disappointed that the single book value packs are no longer an option. I have 20 students in my class and loved being able to buy eac student in my class a book each month for around $20. This year I asked for sponsors for each of the 10 months we are in school. I had every month sponsored which meant that my students would get 10 books this school year. I came to buy books for August and September but now I am having to settling for 20 multi-book pack that cost twice as much and having to tell my sponsors that I will not be able to use their donations how I had originally planned. I am extremely disappointed and I know I am not the only teacher that liked to do this. Please consider putting the single book value packs back on your site. I will not be able to financially provide 10 books to my students if the 20 book packs for $40 are my only options. It's especially frustrating because if I set a due date with parents for after the date that is listed,  Scholastic will automatically submit any orders at the end of the month that are sitting in my cart before the order is due and it messes up my coupons and cumulative bonus points I would have received. I would have already had an order due for earlier this month, but now feel like I have to wait until the due date, so I don't confuse parents since the date would be different on the website than what I am telling them.
